01:03:30.387 --> 01:03:33.727
Is being called "Noona"
such a shocking incident?

01:03:36.057 --> 01:03:37.627
I know. I feel the same way.

01:03:37.757 --> 01:03:38.873
- Right?
- Yes.

01:03:38.897 --> 01:03:42.167
Gosh, this is... It's simply...

01:03:42.797 --> 01:03:46.437
It's not like a pet name.
You're just addressing someone.

01:03:46.667 --> 01:03:49.107
It's a way to address someone,
but suddenly, from that...

01:03:49.707 --> 01:03:52.547
Like, all of a sudden, she
seems to have woken up.

01:03:52.847 --> 01:03:54.947
"How many years are we apart?"

01:03:55.117 --> 01:03:56.923
"When I hear this man's age,"

01:03:56.947 --> 01:03:59.293
"will I still be able to
feel attracted to him?"

01:03:59.317 --> 01:04:01.017
I think I've felt that way before too.

01:04:01.317 --> 01:04:02.793
Not in a relationship,

01:04:02.817 --> 01:04:05.157
mas quando alguém
demonstra interesse por mim.

01:04:05.387 --> 01:04:08.497
Eu também quero namorar a pensar em casamento.

01:04:08.727 --> 01:04:10.203
Mas perguntei-me: "Será que posso
simplesmente namorar casualmente assim?"

01:04:10.227 --> 01:04:13.397
Tornou-me sensível
até às mínimas coisas.

01:04:16.067 --> 01:04:18.437
(Monte Nam)

01:04:19.267 --> 01:04:22.377
(Segurando um bilhete para o
teleférico na mão,)

01:04:22.877 --> 01:04:26.207
(A mulher mais velha aguarda o seu encontro
no Monte Nam, um local que lhe traz boas recordações.)

01:04:27.107 --> 01:04:31.153
(E um homem mais novo chega ao Monte Nam.)

01:04:31.177 --> 01:04:32.487
Finalmente, Sang Won...

01:04:34.117 --> 01:04:35.987
- Ji Won?
- O quê?

01:04:36.487 --> 01:04:42.603
(A primeira de duas fotos na gaveta de Sang Won)

01:04:42.627 --> 01:04:44.827
(Ji Won)

01:04:45.467 --> 01:04:48.227
(Ji Won cumprimenta Sang
Won com um sorriso radiante.)

01:04:49.867 --> 01:04:51.913
